  "text": "where r = (x, y) and q = (q x , q y ) represent the real space and reciprocal space coordinates respectively, ⊗ is the correlation operator, * indicates the complex conjugate, and p is the correlation power law coefficient. The crosscorrelation is given when p = 0, and phase correlation is defined by p = 1. Values of p between 0 and 1 define a hybrid image correlation [CITATION_1] .",
